description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you are interested in developing your General and Project Management skills, this is an ideal opportunity. The Clinical Support Division is looking for a Deputy General Manager/Project Manager on a fixed term, full time (37.5 hours) to join their team. The post holder will be responsible for working with divisional management teams on the Divisional Governance agenda and day to day operational management. The post holder will also work with our well-established cancer project team on both the 28 day Faster Diagnosis and Living with &amp; Beyond Cancer implementation. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Clinical Support Division consists of 4 Directorates – Cancer Services, Pharamcy, Daignosticw (Radiology + Pathology) and Patient access. The post holder will provide management leadership and expert advice to the administration teams within the Division and will support the Divisional Clinical Lead on the Governance Agenda. They will also be responsible for the implementation of specific projects within Cancer Services.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further details / informal visits contact: Jo Clutterbuck, Cancer Services Manager; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Joanna.clutterbuck@wvt.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;; Tel 07813 538785&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
